  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How should I handle a telephone interview?",
  "response": "Handling a telephone interview effectively requires preparation, professionalism, and confidence. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you succeed:\n\n---\n\n### **Before the Interview**\n1. **Research the Company and Role**  \n   - Understand the company\u2019s mission, values, and recent news.  \n   - Review the job description to align your skills and experiences with their needs.\n\n2. **Prepare Your Answers**  \n   - Practice common interview questions (e.g., \"Tell me about yourself,\" \"Why do you want this role?\").  \n   - Use the **STAR method** (Situation, Task, Action, Result) for behavioral questions.  \n\n3. **Gather Your Materials**  \n   - Keep your resume, job description, and any prepared notes in front of you.  \n   - Have a pen and paper ready to jot down important points or questions.\n\n4. **Choose a Quiet Space**  \n   - Find a quiet, distraction-free environment with good phone reception.  \n\n5. **Test Your Phone Connection**  \n   - Ensure your phone is charged and working properly.  \n\n6. **Warm Up Your Voice**  \n   - Practice speaking clearly and confidently. Smiling while speaking can make you sound more engaging.\n\n---\n\n### **During the Interview**\n1. **Answer Professionally**  \n   - Address the interviewer by name (if provided) and speak clearly and confidently.  \n   - Avoid interrupting the interviewer.  \n\n2. **Use Your Notes Thoughtfully**  \n   - Refer to your notes sparingly\u2014don\u2019t sound like you\u2019re reading from a script.  \n\n3. **Ask Questions**  \n   - Prepare thoughtful questions about the role, team, or company (e.g., \"What does success look like in this position?\").  \n\n4. **Listen Actively**  \n   - Pay attention to the interviewer\u2019s tone and cues. Take notes if needed.  \n\n5. **Be Positive and Enthusiastic**  \n   - Show genuine interest in the role and company.  \n\n---\n\n### **After the Interview**\n1. **Thank the Interviewer**  \n   - Express gratitude for their time and reiterate your interest in the role.  \n\n2. **Follow Up**  \n   - Send a thank-you email within 24 hours, restating your enthusiasm and key qualifications.  \n\n---\n\n### **Additional Tips**\n- **Dress Professionally**: It helps put you in the right mindset.  \n- **Speak Slowly and Clearly**: Phone interviews can sometimes distort your voice.  \n- **Avoid Background Noise**: Close windows, silence notifications, and keep pets away.  \n\nBy preparing thoroughly and staying calm, you\u2019ll make a great impression during your telephone interview. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
